Name: n-Nonacosane
Description: Nonacosane is a straight-chain alkane comprising of 29 carbon atoms. It has a role as a plant metabolite and a volatile oil component.

fish_seafood_concentrations.References: (1) Al-Hassan JM et al; Bull Environ Contam Toxicol 66: 646-52 (2001) (2) Pena E et al; Bull Environ Contam Toxicol 61: 72-9 (1998) (3) Pena E et al; Bull Environ Contam Toxicol 63: 665-72 (1999)
fish_seafood_concentrations.Value: Catfish samples collected from seven locations in the Arabian Gulf had concentrations of C29 alkanes (possibly nonacosane) ranging from not detected to 2.2 ng/g wet weight(1). Mean nonacosane concentrations of 265.9, 132.4, and 207.7 ng/g dry weight were reported in intertidal limpet (Patella ulyssiponensis) from 3 sampling stations in the Canary Islands during 1991-1993(2). Mean nonacosane concentrations of 505.3, 333, and 493 ng/g dry weight were reported in intertidal limpet (Patella crenata) collected during May 1991-December 1993 at 3 sampling stations in the Canary Islands (3).

sediment_soil_concentrations.Value: SEDIMENT: Nonacosane concentrations were 20-708 ng/g dry weight in sediments samples collected from 14 sites from the Shinano River in Niigata Japan from November 2005 to April 2006(1).
